==English==
===Noun===
'''dike''' (''plural:'' '''dikes''')

#(''also spelled'' [[dyke]]) A barrier of stone or earth used to hold back water and prevent flooding.
#(''rare'') Variant spelling of [[dyke]], a lesbian.
#(''Geology'') A body of once molten [[igneous]] [[rock]] that was injected into older rocks in a manner that crosses bedding planes.

====Synonyms====
''' barrier of stone or earth'''
*[[levee]]
*[[floodwall]]

